Air Compressors and Rigs




Products
When it comes to rock drilling, Atlas Copco has explored all the angles. Centuries of experience and expertise is reflected in our range of rock drilling tools. Our commitment is to continue to develop, manufacture and distribute the highest quality, most cost-effective rock drilling tools for the mining, construction and oil & gas drilling industries.

We are committed to providing state-of-the-art matrix and steel body PDC bits, as well as a number of other drilling products, that optimize drilling efficiency and lower drilling costs through quality performance. Our fully-equipped manufacturing facility, staffed with an experienced engineering design team, management and technicians is using proprietary systems and processes to build the industry's highest quality PDC bits and drilling products. We are continually improving product design, performance and durability by developing innovative solutions for today's drilling challenges.
Innovative designs
Atlas Copco oil & gas product design engineers and designers are always looking for new and innovative designs for today's drilling challenges. Whether it is our new, more stable curve bit designs, innovative PDC reamer designs, frac plug drill-out bits, or the Klaw bit design, there are always product improvements in R&D preparing for commercial release.
Deep leach PDC cutters
Through collaboration with MegaDiamond, Atlas Copco PDC bits now include deep leach cutters for those applications that require a longer lasting, more thermally stable PDC cutter. Deep leach cutters allow operators to drill further and faster, with the cutter staying sharper than traditional non-leached cutters.
 
Bit stability modeling
Our in-house engineering team has created a proprietary bit stability modeling software suite. This program allows the design team to run various drilling scenarios using the bit design throughout the design process. The program allows the engineering team to understand which bit designs allow for most stability and efficient drilling in different drilling applications. Some of the drilling scenarios calculated by the program include:

Off-center rotation
Abnormal force absorption
Off-axis rotation

Collaborative product designing
Rather than just designing generic bits for applications, Altas Copco sales and engineering teams will work with operators to design bits tailored to fit the specific drilling application. New designs can be generated and reviewed by the customer before it is completed so they can provide further input and feedback on the design and its features. With quick turnaround, new designs and products can be completed in a matter of weeks, instead of months like with many other bit manufacturers. 



 



